Here's a quick update for you: Personal Best notifications during mini-games. Now there's no excuse not to beat your old score.

Also, we've made performance improvements for iOS 8 and fixed a little audio glitch. Enjoy!

• We've added ReplayKit support for iOS9 - so record all your finest table tennis battles and crazy mini-game high scores.
• There's a brand new arena in Multiplayer - the Nightclub! The UV lights are on and the fantastic new glowing "Earth" table is waiting for you.
• 4 new bat skins to win - Oh Canada, Evil Knight, Ice Cream and a festive skin, Santa Bat!
• To ease newer players into multiplayer, we've limited multiplayer bat selection to only allow you to play with the best bat that BOTH of you have unlocked.
• We've made lots of behind-the-scenes savings to reduce the app size by 70MB, which is nice.
• Fixed a bug that affected some images on A9 devices.

Happy Holidays everyone! See you next year!

Christmas may be over but we have some New Year goodies for you...

• Quick Game - you can now choose which arena you want to play in. Choose from any of the 9 arenas (including the snazzy new nightclub one).
• Voice Chat has been added to online multiplayer! Awesome.
• More flags - we had a lot of emails requesting extra flags so we've added 18 more!
• Say goodbye to Entry Stakes - now if you lose a Throwdown, you'll no longer lose R.
• Tutorial - this has moved over to the Options screen which makes a lot more sense.
• New mini game 'How To Play' screens - they now also include a very useful tip from Wiff Waff which we recommend you check out.
• Bat control info screens - these have all been updated to make it much clearer what all the different options do.

This version has a lot of behind-the-scenes game engine changes, fixes and improvements. That means that multiplayer is not backwards compatible so you definitely want to grab this update to continue playing your friends.

Go hit some balls!

Big news - Update #9 for Table Tennis Touch brings you language support!

Now choose to play in either French, German, Italian, Spanish, Russian, Turkish, Brazilian Portuguese, Japanese, Korean or Chinese. Lovely stuff.

But that's not all...we've also added more bat skins, added game selection back into Quick Game, made lots of little changes to make the game even better for you and squished some bugs.

Thanks everyone for your support and keep the feedback coming!
